history.text: Hello~
Hello
Do you like superhero films?
I do like them for the most part.  The Marvel movies are good.  How about you?
Love them! One of my favorite is Batman begins
Have you seen it?
I have seen it and it is definitely one of may favorites!  I love that they handle the origin story of Batman in a very realistic way.
What do you like most about it?
Christian Bale plays Bruce Wayne and he is wonderful!
Christian Bale does do a very convincing job of playing the part.  The emotions that he shows while regaining his abilities and life is so true
Do you like Liam Neeson's portrayal of Ra's al Ghul?

Yes, I like Liam a lot. My boyfriend
 not so much.
I didn't think the other movies touched on his fear of bats like this one
I agree with the approach to a fear of bats.  They really took it back to the beginning (no pun intended) of when he started fearing bats and how he used it as a positive.
Can you imagine have both of your parents murdered infront of you? How horrific!
That would be terrible!  I do like the plot line that he takes that horrible event and uses it to get stronger!
I think that Michael Caine is an amazing Alfred!
One of my favorite scenes is when Bruce comes back and is playing golf with the secretary in the board room.
What is your favorite scene?
He sure is! Batman is like the classic superhero using the bad things that happened to him to be better
Probably the training scenes where you get an idea of how much inner rage he has learned to contain
Yeah, I love how his psyche is damaged but he just keeps going and pushing with the revenge factor.
I can't believe that movie is already 10 years old!
It is crazy that it has been around that long.  I love all of the movies in that series by Christopher Nolan!
Can you believe that it only got a metacritic score of 70/100?!
What would you give it?
No I cant really. But it still got an A for a cenema score. I'd give a 90/100
And rotten tomatoes with a 7.7/10. Thy're some tough critics
Yes they are.
I'm so amazed by Gary Oldman's portrayal in it.
He did great. I wasnt so cure i liked Katie Holmes all the way though
I'm not sure I like her in general as an actress anymore
Yeah, she was ok, but not great.  She paled in comparison to the other great performances!
I really liked the idea of the technology of the microwave emitter.  It was definitely believable.
